article.headline: Kent St. 77, Buffalo 71
article.story: OXFORD, Ohio -- Al Fisher scored 15 points, including six in a row in overtime, to lead Kent State to a 77-71 victory over Buffalo on Thursday night. Chris Singletary, who led the Golden Flashes (18-13, 10-6 Mid-American Conference) with 19 points, hit two free throws with 16 seconds left in regulation to tie the game at 67. Buffalo's Rodney Pierce missed a 3-pointer with 2 seconds left. In the overtime, Fisher hit two foul shots at the 1:41 mark for a 71-68 lead, then hit a layup with 29 seconds remaining and added two more free throws with 22 seconds left for a 75-69 Kent State lead. Jordan Mincy, who had 13 points, added two clinching free throws with 2 seconds remaining. Julian Sullinger chipped in with 12 points and 11 rebounds. Greg Gamble had 17 points, Pierce had 16, Andy Robinson 13 and Mitchell Watt 10 for the Bulls (18-11, 10-6).
